porate PR and governmental policies. Authors are academics and artists. The result is a new mapping of the intermingling and co-constitution of aesthetics and politics in engagements with collective orders.  afunded by Technische Universität Berlin  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aCultural Theory. 4aGovernance. 4aInnovation. 4aPolitical Sociology. 4aPolitical Theory. 4aPolitics. 4aPractices. 4aSenses. 4aSociety. 4aSociology of Culture. 4aSociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aCultural Theory.  aGovernance.  aInnovation.  aPolitical Sociology.  aPolitical Theory.  aPolitics.  aPractices.  aSenses.  aSociety.  aSociology of Culture.  aSociology.1 aAustin, Jonathan Luke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeermann, Rose, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBinner, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarfán, Vanessa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuggenheim, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaulsen, Aline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHennion, Antoine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHusberg, Hanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLandau-Donnelly, Friederike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeander, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarzecová, Agata, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMitrović, Mirjana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/v